                <h3 class="subheading">1. Stricter Speed Limit Enforcement</h3>
                <p>New AI-based speed cameras have been installed across highways and cities to automatically detect speed violations. Speeding fines have been significantly increased, and repeat offenders may face license suspension.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">2. Mandatory Seat Belt for All Passengers</h3>
                <p>It is now compulsory for rear-seat passengers to wear seat belts. Failing to follow this rule can result in hefty fines for both the passenger and the driver.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">3. Heavy Penalties for Mobile Phone Usage While Driving</h3>
                <p>Using mobile phones while driving is now a serious offence. The fines have doubled in 2025, and in some cases, the driver's license may be temporarily suspended for repeated violations.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">4. New Helmet Rules for Two-Wheeler Riders</h3>
                <p>Both the rider and pillion on two-wheelers must wear BIS-certified helmets. Non-compliance will lead to immediate fines, and using substandard helmets is also punishable.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">5. Revised Learner's License Process</h3>
                <p>Getting a learner's license in 2025 has become easier with online application and testing. However, the new system is stricter, ensuring drivers understand road safety before getting a permanent license.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">6. Changes in Vehicle Registration and Fitness Validity</h3>
                <p>Old vehicles now need to pass regular fitness tests. If a vehicle fails the test, it may need to be scrapped under the new vehicle scrappage policy. Private vehicles older than 15 years must undergo mandatory inspections.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">7. Digital Driving License and RC Validity</h3>
                <p>Drivers can now legally carry digital copies of their driving license and RC using government apps like mParivahan and DigiLocker. Physical copies are no longer mandatory if verified through these apps.</p>

                <h3 class="subheading">8. Electric Vehicle (EV) Friendly Policies</h3>
                <p>Some cities in India are introducing special lanes and parking spots for electric vehicles. Additionally, EV owners may receive discounts on toll charges and road tax.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Technology-Driven Enforcement in 2025</h2>
                <div class="row m-b20">
                    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 text-center"><img src="~/images/blogs/2025/july/new driving rules/hefty fine.webp" alt="bikecarhubtvsapache" title="bikecarhubtvsapache" /></div>
                </div>
                <p>The transport authorities in India have upgraded their traffic enforcement systems in 2025. New technologies now play a major role in catching violators quickly.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">AI-Based Speed Cameras:</span> Automatically detect and record over-speeding.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Automated Number Plate Recognition (ANPR):</span> Instantly identifies vehicles breaking the rules.</li>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">E-Challan System:</span> Paperless fines are directly sent to the violator's registered mobile number.</li>
                </ul>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">How to Adapt to the New Driving Rules</h2>
